title: For Sale/Trade:  Rock River Arms Predator Pursuit BMG two tone AR-15 long range .223 Vortex Harris Hornady ammo case sling
postcontent: I am looking to sell or trade a compact long range precision AR-15. This is a tack driver of a gun. The lower is built by Bend Manufacturing Group, it is their Raptor lower and is a very high quality precision lower. It is outfitted with a Rock River Arms two stage trigger, a Noveske 60 degree safety, an extended bolt lock, a Magpul enhanced trigger guard, an an FDE ERGO grip, and fitted with a mil-spec 6 position buffer tube with single point sling ring and Magpul FDE MOE stock. The upper is a factory built Rock River Arms Predator Pursuit with a 16 inch heavy barreled Wylde chamber 1 in 8 twist. This will stabilize about the entire range of .223 bullet weights and chamber either .223 or 5.56 NATO. It has a picatinney rail on top of the gas block for mounting of a BUIS or light/laser etc and is currently protected by a rail ladder The bolt and carrier are chromed for reliability and ease of cleaning, the charge handle is a BCM extended catch for ease of charging with a scope. I had the free floated fore end ceramicoated in FDE to complete the two tone by HD Hydrographics in Redmond. Bi-pod is a Harris with the swivel and notched legs and enough extension to clear the ground when using a 30 round mag. Magazine is a 30 round Magpul PMAG in FDE with black Ranger Plate. The scope is a Vortex PST 2.5-10X32 with the EBR-1 (MRAD) reticle. It is a first focal plane and has 10 illumination settings. Graduated in MOA and very clear optics. Small front objective keeps your signature down, and power is low enough for rapid acquisition or medium to long range precision. Comes with the original box, paperwork, covers, scope cloth and all. It is mounted on a set of Warne Maxima steel rings with quick disconnects, also with original packaging. Package will come with the Soft-Armor tactical bag which has 5 STANAG magazine pouches and a large accessory pouch, nice reinforced carry strap, and heavy reliable padding and zipper. Also included is the 3.5 boxes of Hornady match ammo, 75 grain boat tail, perfect for this gun and the installed single point bungee sling. This gun is ridiculous accurate, I regularly shoot 12 GA. hulls off fence posts at 150 yards, it is nothing but the best of the best for an accuracy AR-15.

title: For Sale:  CLONE Benchmade Infidel 3300 OTF Black - How to spot...
postcontent:
I discovered that a Benchmade Infidel that I traded for was actually a fake (didn't find out until I went to sell it and someone pointed it out).  Fortunately, I didn't trade much for it.  Looking around, there seem to be a lot of fakes out there, and plenty of slimeballs selling them as real ones.  I was told by several folks that mine is the best looking fake clone they have seen, so be careful.  That being said, even being a fake, it's still pretty impressive.

I've had really good luck with folks on armslist, so hopefully I can provide some tips for spotting a fake.  Easiest is to go to youtube and search "Benchmade Infidel - Fake Vs. Real."  In summary:

1.  The clip was the only visual giveaway on mind.  The real ones have a butterfly on the bent clip at the tip, and mine does not.  The anodizing of the letters is also different.

2.  The fake ones are a lot heavier.  Of course, you can only tell this if you are buying face to face.  The real ones way about 5 ounces (per manufacturer).  My clone is 7.5 ounces...pretty significant.

3.  There are apparently some other finish differences, though I am told mine is a pretty darn good match.

Hope all this helps.  I am still willing to sell it, if nothing else, to keep this listing active and educate folks.  Do your homework!

title: For Sale:  SOLD-1943 CAI imported Russian Izhevsk Mosin Nagant M91/30 Round Receiver  -7.62x54R w/ Matching Serial #'s and Case
postcontent:
SOLD

Note: Interested parties must pick up rifle in Dallas, TX. Cash only (no checks, cc, paypal or trades).


This Century International Arms imported WWII rifle is a Izhevsk made Russian M91/30 Mosin Nagant in 1943 with a great bore. All serial #'s match on the Bolt, Butt Plate, Trigger Guard, & Receiver. This rifle is in good condition by NRA standards and shoots just as it should, which is to say that it is extremely accurate shooting the Russian surplus ammo I purchased. I still have a bulk of that ammo available for purchase if you're looking to buy quality ammo at a reduced price. I meticulously removed cosmoline from every nook and cranny on this rifle-- which was laid on thick when I received it. Comes with a plastic case and everything pictured. 

These are very durable, reliable and accurate rifles. It also looks very impressive with the bayonet extended. The M91/30 rifle was developed after the Germans overran and killed thousands of Soviet soldiers equipped with the M38 carbine which had no provisions for a bayonet. The M91/30 was intended to be issued to all soldiers, replacing not only carbines but rifles as well. The M91/30 was used by many countries following the war, and was a favorite of the Israeli Haganah.

Here's the full description from Sig:

The 1911 STX from the SIG SAUER Custom Shop is a two-tone 1911 that’s loaded with features. This non-railed pistol features a Nitron® slide over a Natural Stainless frame and is accented by beautiful custom wood grips. The slide is further accented by polished cocking serrations and a Flat Top which enhances the two-tone aspect of this pistol. The slide is topped off with adjustable combat night sights while the frame is outfitted with a magwell for fast smooth reloads. The all stainless steel frame and slide of the STX are machined to exacting tolerances and hand-fitted to insure reliability and performance. The frame features 25-line per inch checkering on the front strap – while the mainspring housing has 20-line per inch checkering – and both the frame and slide are de-horned for comfortable full-size carry. Like all SIG SAUER products the 1911 STX pistol contains only premium internal parts including a match grade barrel, hammer/sear set and trigger. For safety the 1911 STX features a beavertail grip safety with speed bump, extended ambidextrous thumb safety, firing pin safety and hammer intercept notch and ships in a plastic gun case with cable lock.

Will consider trade for .45 acp Glock, full size or compact, plus some cash or ammo on your end.  No lowball offers please, I definitely know what my gun is worth...
